column7: Principles, concepts and tools used in plant breeding. Includes methods and breeding schemes used with different plant species. Additional fees may apply. See Class Schedule. 4 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite: IB 103; CPSC 352 or equivalent.
